Uses of Package
com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient

  • Packages that use com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient 
    Package Description
    com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient  
    com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient.internal.commandinterceptors  
  • Classes in com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient used by com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient 
    Class and Description
    ClientTransactionIdStrategy
    Bean, used when a command is sent from a DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server, to generate a client transaction id to be put in the meta-data.
    DNSAPIClient
    Instance of a DNSAPI client, used to send a command to the DNAPI server, and get a Response back from it.
    ObjectMapperFactory
    The factory used to create ObjectMapper instances, used by the created DNSAPIClient instances to serialize and deserialize the JSON data sent to or coming from the DNSAPI server.
    Response
    The response coming back from the DNSAPI Server, consequently to a sent command.
    SSLContextFactory
    The factory used to create SSLContext instances, to establish secure communications between the created DNSAPIClient instances and the DNSAPI server.
    TransactionLogHandler
    The bean used to log the transactions between the DNSAPIClient instances and the DNSAPI server.
  • Classes in com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient used by com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient.internal.commandinterceptors

    TransactionLogHandler
    The bean used to log the transactions between the DNSAPIClient instances and the DNSAPI server.
